3. Physics & Science Lessons
This transcript leverages specific concepts from advanced physics to propose a theoretical drive system:
A. Quantum Momentum & Phase
In quantum mechanics, particles behave as waves. The "phase" of a wave determines how it interferes with other waves. The text suggests that by manipulating the phase relationships of entangled particles (qubits), one can generate a net directional force (momentum). This is similar to the concept of a Quantum Drive or vacuum thruster, though highly theoretical.
B. The Planck Scale
The engine operates at the Planck scale (
