C. Conservation of Momentum (Reinterpreted)
Standard physics dictates you must throw mass out the back to move forward (Newton's Third Law). This text suggests a loophole: if momentum is derived from the spin of the quantum field itself, you don't need reaction mass. You are "pushing" against the geometry of spacetime rather than pushing against fuel.
D. Angular Frequency as Energy
The text correctly cites the relationship between energy and frequency (
