). It teaches that "spin" is not just rotation but a fundamental energy carrier. If you can control spin, you control energy; if you control energy, you control motion.
E. Holographic Entanglement
This references the idea that the volume of space is encoded on a lower-dimensional boundary (the screen). The engine mimics a black hole's geometry to access the high-energy density of the singularity/horizon relationship.
4. Summary
The "Entanglement Engine" is a theoretical propulsion system based on Quantum Information Holography. Instead of burning fuel, it uses a quantum computer as an engine. By arranging qubits in concentric shells and entangling them, the engine creates standing waves of probability. By systematically shifting the phase and spin of these qubits, the engine converts quantum angular momentum directly into macroscopic thrust. This would allow for a silent, fuel-free vessel capable of constant 1g acceleration, eventually reaching relativistic speeds by manipulating the fundamental geometry of light and space.